            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001846_0001" n="0001"/>
<opener>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U1">MS 8/8</add>
<lb/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U1">5-6-9</add><!-- diagonal --> <dateline><space extent="1" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><orig>Quillimane</orig><reg>Quelimane</reg></choice></settlement></placeName> <date when="1862-11-19">19<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>November</expan></choice>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>1862</date></dateline>   
<lb/><salute>My Dear Sunley</salute>
</opener>

<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>We left you
<lb/>on <choice><sic>Wedensday</sic><corr>Wednesday</corr></choice> and were down
<lb/>within <measure>30 miles</measure> of the <placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName>
<lb/>on Monday, but our coals were
<lb/>expended and the wind being
<lb/>contrary we bore away to the
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Quillimane</orig><reg>Quelimane</reg></choice> River</geogName></placeName> to cut wood
<lb/>We saw <persName>Prince Mahomet</persName>s
<lb/>boat close in shore about half
<lb/>past one - we were scarcely a
<lb/>mile from the beach and a
<lb/>heavy sea was beating towards
<lb/>the land. I ran up the <term type="occupation">ensign</term>
<lb/>to the masthead and doubled
<lb/>back on our course as a hint
<lb/>to him to come out to us but he
<lb/>paid no attention &amp; held on
<lb/>towards the town. I was afraid</p>
<!-- The following continues on from the end of the letter. AW -->
<cb rend="vertical left"/><ab>
<lb/>then if he does not do well it is his own look out
<lb/><persName>Rae</persName> has just come to say that the negotiation
</ab>
	
	<pb facs="liv_001846_0002" n="0002"/>	
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">of running on the reef if we
<lb/>approached him. We then went
<lb/>on to the town and saw a boat
<lb/>attempt to put off and give up
<lb/>the case as hopeless - the heavy
<lb/>sea was breaking on the reef
<lb/>I felt sorry I could not deliver
<lb/>your message to <persName>Prince Mahomet</persName> 
<lb/>but the obstinate way in which
<lb/>he held on his course when he
<lb/>could have come out to us in
<lb/>half an hour convinced me that
<lb/>he was led by his less worthy
<lb/>companion. The glass was
<lb/>lower than we had seen it at
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> and as it would have
<lb/>been a useless risk of life to
<lb/>land we hurried on and by
<lb/>evening had got into a much
<lb/>calmer sea. I had ordered a</p>
<cb rend="vertical left"/><ab>
<lb/>for the engine and sugar mill seems to</ab>


	<pb facs="liv_001846_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">man called <persName>Abdullah</persName> to get
<lb/>fresh meat - fowls - vegetables &amp;c<!-- and cetera? -AA --><!-- Correct. AW -->	
<lb/>and bring them off without
<lb/>waiting to come off to be told
<lb/>what to bring - If you will
<lb/>kindly pay him for what
<lb/>he expended I shall feel much
<lb/>obliged - I am anxious that he
<lb/>does not lose by trusting to my
<lb/>word - The amount would be
<lb/>about 30 <choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice> of <term type="foodstuff">meat</term> 2 dozen
<lb/><term type="animal_foodstuff">fowls</term> with a few bushels of
<lb/><term type="plant_foodstuff">potatoes</term> - <term type="plant_foodstuff">cassava</term> &amp;c<!-- and cetera? -AA --><!-- Correct. AW -->. <persName>Abdullah</persName>
<lb/>is a sort of <term type="occupation">factotum</term> of the
<lb/><term type="occupation">Queen</term> &amp; general <term type="occupation">interpreter</term></p>            	
<lb/><p>I am in <persName>Colonel Nunes</persName> house
<lb/>and have given your invitation
<lb/>with which he seems much
<lb/>pleased - We see <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <del type="strikethrough">crew</del> Crux</persName>'s
<lb/>field of <term type="plant_foodstuff">Bourbon sugar cane</term>
<lb/>totally neglected. and the size
<lb/>of rat's tents - It is moreover
<lb/>planted in a sandy salt place -
<lb/>The <unclear cert="low">olen</unclear> look well &amp; the <orgName><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> 
<lb/>men</orgName> are doing well.</p>
<cb rend="vertical right"/><ab>
<lb/>going on favourably
</ab>
            	
	<pb facs="liv_001846_0004" n="0004"/>            	
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="marginleft">4</add> of our <term type="nationality">English</term> <term type="occupation">crew</term> had to <supplied cert="high">be</supplied> brought
<lb/>down to the ship by <term type="occupation">soldiers</term>
<lb/>victims of grog. We have met
<lb/>the Rapid here with <persName>Captain
<lb/>Jago</persName> whom you may remember
<lb/>as first <term type="occupation">Lieutenant</term> of the
<lb/>Hermes - We could not send the	
<lb/>cattle overland from this
<lb/>and will go in a day or two to
<lb/>the <placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> - The river has
<lb/>not yet begun to rise. <persName>Rae</persName>
<lb/>has had a little touch of <term type="ailment">fever</term>
<lb/>otherwise we are all well -</p>          	
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">With kind recollections of
<lb/>your kindness I am most
<lb/>sincerely yours <persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p>P.S. <persName>Robert</persName> my eldest boy is going
<lb/>to <placeName>Edinburgh College</placeName>. I suppose <persName><choice><abbr>Prof</abbr><expan>Professor</expan></choice>
<lb/>Playfair</persName> has obtained influence over
<lb/>him. This agrees with my desire to
<lb/>give him a good education &amp;</p> <!--This text spills onto page 1 as vertical text. -AA -->	<!--I cannot seem to make the postscript code work, no matter where I put it. Is the manual's example correct? If so, does it go inside or outside the closer? -AA --><!-- I cannot offer any clarity here and would be interested to know the correct way of encoding this, JM --><!-- See how I've done this. The trick is to use <postscript> plus <p>. Also, the closer ends here although technically it continues on to the first page. On the first page, I have marked the additional bit as part of the closer. AW -->
	
	

            </div>
